card.name: Permitting workflow Study
card.desc:
This team saw the need to create a workflow to help better understand how the end user would search for, access and manage permits - including administrative managers within the Forest Service - and end users wanting a permit from a specific forest. 

Study the 'big picture' in permitting and the end users access, so that we can find ways to improve the end users search for a specific permit for a specific forest more quickly, expand SEO exposure for better  -more clear-  SE search results, and help identify a good solution for Administrative permit management.

VALUE ADDED: The effort will help the team 

1. Better understand how users access permitting sites 
2. Help identify possible workflow improvements for users
3. Ultimately help end users more quickly and easily find a specific permit through better SEO with multiple pages referencing permits
4. Understand the value of easier access to analyze traffic and user patterns within the Open Forest system vs outside the Open Forest system
5. Clearly define first steps for admin users to potentially access and manage all their apps from one simple interface from the Open Forest landing page
6. Plan how this project can take advantage of temple driven development by identifying pages that will be reused within each forest and plan accordingly.

card.name: Permitting workflow "big picture"
card.desc:
This team saw the need to create a workflow to help better understand how the end user would search for, access and manage permits - including administrative managers within the Forest Service - and end users wanting a permit from a specific forest. 

Study the 'big picture' in permitting and the end users access, so that we can find ways to improve the end users search for a specific permit for a specific forest more quickly, expand SEO exposure for better  -more clear-  SE search results, and help identify a good solution for Administrative permit management.

VALUE ADDED: The effort will help the team 

1. Better understand how users access permitting sites 
2. Help identify possible workflow improvements for users
3. Ultimately help end users more quickly and easily find a specific permit through better SEO with multiple pages referencing permits
4. Understand the value of easier access to analyze traffic and user patterns within the Open Forest system vs outside the Open Forest system
5. Clearly define first steps for admin users to potentially access and manage all their apps from one simple interface from the Open Forest landing page
6. Plan how this project can take advantage of temple driven development by identifying pages that will be reused within each forest and plan accordingly.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:

- Workflows created (three options)
- One workflow was chosen and agreed upon by team members
- PO has reviewed and approved final workflow

Study the 'big picture' in permitting and the end users access, so that we can find ways to improve the end users search for a specific permit for a specific forest more quickly, expand SEO exposure for better  -more clear-  SE search results, and help identify a good solution for Administrative permit management.

VALUE ADDED: The effort will help the team 

1. Better understand the big picture for Open Forest to reduce redundancy and wasted development and planning time.
2. Help identify possible workflow improvements for users
3. Ultimately help end users more quickly and easily find a specific permit through better SEO with multiple pages referencing permits
4. Analytics can be more easily tracked and managed within the Open Forest system
5. How admin users can potentially access and manage all their apps from one simple interface from the Open Forest landing page
6. Plan how this project can take advantage of temple driven development by identifying pages that will be reused within each forest and plan accordingly.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:

1. Workflow is created to study by PO and designer and team members interested
2. Changes are made to that workflow from input
3. Final workflow is finalized and approved by Product owner

This team saw the need to create a workflow to help better understand how the end user would search for, access and manage permits - including administrative managers within the Forest Service - and end users wanting a permit from a specific forest.

1. Better understand how users access permitting sites 
2. Help identify possible workflow improvements for users
3. Ultimately help end users more quickly and easily find a specific permit through better SEO with multiple pages referencing permits
4. Understand the value of easier access to analyze traffic and user patterns within the Open Forest system vs outside the Open Forest system
5. Clearly define first steps for admin users to potentially access and manage all their apps from one simple interface from the Open Forest landing page
6. Plan how this project can take advantage of temple driven development by identifying pages that will be reused within each forest and plan accordingly.
